The South African Federation of Trade Unions General Secretary, Zwelinzima Vavi, has tested positive for Coronavirus. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Saftu General Secretary Zwelinzima Vavi has tested positive for COVID-19, he revealed on Thursday. "All I had was a flu from Friday and it got worse by Saturday, Sunday. So I went to test just to be on the safe side. "Not that I had any of the big signs like chest or respiratory problems, no nothing. Just a flu feeling a little bit down and out of my stride." READ: ACDP leader Kenneth Meshoe tests positive for COVID-19 He said he has no idea where he could have come into contact with the virus. Vavi said he is in self-isolation until he recovers. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.